# NEVER commit private GPG / RSA keys.
# generate-keypair.sh writes these to a DEST_DIR you choose at runtime;
# this guard is a belt-and-braces measure for anyone who accidentally
# runs it inside the repo (e.g. `./generate-keypair.sh .` instead of
# `./generate-keypair.sh /tmp/keys/`).
privkey.gpg
privkey.gpg.asc
*.secret-key
*.private
*.gnupg
.gpg-tmp/
.abuild/
keyid.txt
fingerprint.txt
